    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''What Happens if We Leave Iraq?'' (letters, May 30):</p>
        <p>President Bush et al. can read the writing on the wall. They know perfectly well that the war in Iraq is lost and that our troops must eventually withdraw, leaving behind unspeakable chaos in their wake.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''What Happens if We Leave Iraq?'' (letters, May 30):</p>
        <p>President Bush et al. can read the writing on the wall. They know perfectly well that the war in Iraq is lost and that our troops must eventually withdraw, leaving behind unspeakable chaos in their wake.</p>
        <p>The administration is simply stalling for time until the next election, when it can dump the whole mess in the Democrats' laps.</p>
        <p>Then it can retreat to the sidelines, watch the misery for which it laid the groundwork come to pass, and deliver sound bites along the lines of ''See? I told you what would happen.''</p>
        <p>Carol Haskill  San Francisco, May 30, 2007</p>
      </block>
